thread.title: TV | Enchanted

author: Fiona Flynn
title: TV | Enchanted
text: Yeah okay, there is a bang of a kids movie off this, but it's actually pretty good. No, really! Cartoon world and real world get mixed together, and it makes for a pretty amusing tale. Amy Adams is fantastic as the lost cartoon princess in New York, who is 'rescued' by Patrick Dempsey. Susan Sarandon even makes an appearance as the evil step mother. The musical and dance scene to the song 'That's How You Know' was also nominated for Best Original Song in the Oscars that year. So now, The OSCARS no less. Not so judgmental now, are you.
